author: Unknown
content_text:
Closure Notice ‚Äì Operations Update
To our valued community,
It is with much regret that the Linear Operations Team now write to advise you to leave the project. Many of us have worked alongside you for nearly five years, and we share in the disappointment this brings. While this outcome was not what anyone hoped for, we remain committed to supporting all users during this transition, within the boundaries of the instructions provided by the project‚Äôs owners and investors.
Below you‚Äôll find the essential details to help you safely exit your positions, along with the key dates to be aware of. If you need assistance, support remains available until the closure date‚Äîprimarily via our Telegram group, and secondarily on Discord.
Exit Your Positions
We strongly recommend that all users exit their positions as soon as possible. Liquidity will become increasingly limited over time. Additionally, once Binance completes the delisting of the LINA token, market access may be further reduced.
Shutdown Timeline
Final Closure: Weds, 2 April 2025 at 12:00 PM UTC
At this time, the Linear suite of dApps will go offline, except for a Burn and Unstake Portal, which will remain available to:
- Unstake tokens from staking and exit
- Burn LUSD, if necessary, to clear debt and enable unstaking
Immediate Actions to Take
Locked Staking Rewards
All remaining locked and vesting rewards (originally scheduled to vest over the next 12 months) have been moved to your staked balance. These can now be unstaked and withdrawn, subject to your debt position.
Builder
Repay any outstanding Builder debt and unstake any collateral (LINA or other tokens).
Synthetic Exchange
Remaining liquid assets should be converted to LUSD via the Synthetic Exchange, and then sold on PancakeSwap. Terminal prices for all liquid assets have already been applied. Only conversions into LUSD are now supported.
Bridge
The ETH/BSC and BSC/ETH bridges for LINA and LUSD will close permanently at shutdown. No cross-chain transfers will be possible after this point.
Liquidator
The Liquidator has already been switched off
Marketplace
The Marketplace has already been closed. No active listings remain, aside from those previously managed by the team.
PerpDEX
The PerpDEX will be shut down at the closure time. All users must exit positions and withdraw funds well in advance to avoid potential loss.
Community Channels
Telegram and Discord will remain open until the shutdown date, after which the chat functionality will be disabled.
Thank you for being part of the Linear Finance journey. We are here to support you during this final phase. Please remain respectful to all team members throughout this process.
Sincerely,
The Linear Operations Team

We've been tracking PancakeSwap ($CAKE) closely while many traders got caught in the hype. Despite a broader risk-off environment, $CAKE rallied impressively but was pressing against its major downtrend.

Key factors in our analysis:
- Binance's founder promoting memes on BSC created temporary momentum
- $CAKE as the main DEX became a proxy bet for BSC activity
- Technical resistance aligned perfectly with the downtrend line
- Fundamental limitations of BSC (expensive, slower than Solana ($SOL) or Base)

March 25: CRYPTO MARKET UPDATE
[The Most Published News]
Trump-linked World Liberty Financial (WLFI) has invested $3 million in 3.54 million MNT tokens despite its overall crypto portfolio suffering a loss of about $111 million. In related news, analysts now see upside for XRP following the SEC dropping its longstanding lawsuit against Ripple Labs, forecasting that the token could reach $10 by 2030. Meanwhile, decentralized exchange dYdX‚Äôs announcement of a token buyback using 25% of its monthly net revenue has captured significant attention as it signals confidence in reinforcing its ecosystem.
[Current Market Trends]
PancakeSwap led decentralized exchange activity this week with a 41.93% jump in trading volume‚Äîtotaling $14.1 billion‚Äîwhile Uniswap and Raydium recorded notable declines. Additionally, crypto investment products saw a turnaround after five consecutive weeks of outflows, with inflows amounting to $644 million and spot Bitcoin ETFs reporting robust capital inflows, hinting at a cautiously optimistic sentiment among retail and institutional investors.
[Regulations and Policies]
In a dramatic regulatory development, the SEC‚Äôs decision to drop its lawsuit against Ripple Labs has clarified the outlook for XRP and broader crypto initiatives. Complementing this, a U.S. Senator has proposed a bold plan to eliminate the Federal Reserve, while the Trump administration moves forward with plans to establish a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve. Further stirring the debate, Coinbase‚Äôs Chief Legal Officer criticized the U.S. Treasury‚Äôs handling of the Tornado Cash lawsuit, spotlighting ongoing challenges in the regulatory landscape.
[Technology and Innovation]
Dubai-based DWF Labs has launched a $250 million fund aimed at mid- to large-cap blockchain projects, with an emphasis on overcoming onboarding hurdles and strengthening infrastructure for mainstream crypto adoption. In another innovation push, Ethereum is set to roll out two major upgrades, Pectra and Fusaka, expected to enhance staking efficiency, scalability, and smart contract functionality. Meanwhile, Circle is gearing up to launch its USDC stablecoin in Japan through a partnership with SBI Holdings, marking the first regulated stablecoin introduction in the country.
[Institutional Investor News]
Institutional confidence in crypto is underscored by significant moves in Bitcoin accumulation. Michael Saylor‚Äôs Strategy recently acquired 6,911 BTC‚Äîboosting its total holdings to over 506,000 BTC‚Äîwhile MicroStrategy made a sizeable $584 million Bitcoin purchase to further expand its digital asset portfolio. BlackRock has also deepened its crypto reach by expanding its tokenized money market fund, BUIDL, to the Solana blockchain, reflecting the growing appetite among institutional investors for yield-generating, blockchain-based products.
[Market Forecasts and Expert Opinions]
Market analysts remain bullish on long-term ratings despite short-term volatility. With the SEC lawsuit behind it, XRP is projected to hit $10 by 2030, a forecast supported by potential uplifts from the adoption of Ripple‚Äôs own stablecoin and prospects for an IPO. In addition, QCP Capital highlights historical trends showing that April and Q2 typically favor both risk assets and Bitcoin, suggesting that the current market environment could see renewed positive momentum if macro factors stabilize.
[Security and Hacking News]
Security challenges persist in the crypto space. Dohrnii Labs has filed a police report in the UAE against Blynex, accusing the exchange of unauthorized liquidation of its DHN tokens amid a broader backdrop of market turbulence. In a related development, Movement Network has announced it will use recovered funds‚Äîamounting to $38 million from a rogue market maker misconduct case‚Äîto execute a token buyback program aimed at restoring market stability and investor confidence.
[Conclusion]
Today‚Äôs broad array of crypto news underlines a market in transition. While regulatory clarifications and institutional accumulation signal long-term confidence, caution remains vital amid ongoing volatility‚Äîfrom aggressive trading volumes and derivative products to evolving security concerns. Retail investors are advised to keep a balanced view: monitor key technical levels, remain mindful of regulatory shifts, and consider diversification strategies to navigate an ecosystem marked by both innovation and uncertainty.

If You Think BNB's Meme Culture Is Growing Because Degens Just Chose To Play Here, Then You Need To Stop And Read This.
Over the past 7 days,
@BNBCHAIN
has emerged as the top performer in the Decentralized Exchange Market, surpassing SOL and ETH in volume.
This surge results from these events‚Äîincluding deployments, upgrades, and investments‚Äîthat have been unfolding since the start of Q1:
‚ê• BNB Chain's Pascal Hardfork upgrade.
BNB Chain‚Äôs successful implementation of EIP-7702 through the Pascal Hardfork improved the EVM compatibility & introduced Gasless transactions, Batch approvals & swaps in one click Easier.
This upgrade was pivotal for the onboarding and adoption of the chain, evident on the 7D DEX volume chart.
BNB Chain‚Äôs roadmap doesn‚Äôt stop here, btw.
More upgrades are scheduled for Q2:
üî∏ Lorentz Hardfork (April 2025)
üî∏ Maxwell Hardfork (June 2025)
‚ê• The $2 billion investment from the Arab sovereign fund MGX,
#MUBARAK
This month, Binance announced that it had received a $2 billion investment from the Arab sovereign fund MGX, this led to an Arab cartoon inspired meme ‚ÄúMubarak‚Äù which was quoted by CZ.
This move unexpectedly promoted the steady rise in the price of the newly born meme coin Mubarak on the 13th.
‚ê• The BNB Chain Goodwill Alliance
BNB improved on-chain trading and integrity by creating a community program called 'Goodwill Alliance'.
One of the main or first goals were to eliminate MEV attacks within the BNB ecosystem.
Since this implementation, the average daily volume of sandwich attack transactions on BSC dropped by more than 400%
‚ê• TST Token Phenomenon
The ‚ÄúTest‚Äù token (TST) which was originally designed as a tutorial token for the BNB Chain meme coin launchpad contributed to the ecosystem fee revenue.
The token went as high as $500M market cap, signalling the advent of the BNB meme szn.
‚ê•
@cz_binance
's dog '$BROCCOLI'?
The meme culture was also inspired from Changpeng Zhao's (CZ) post about his dog, Broccoli, which led to the creation of several meme coins named after the dog.
One of these meme coins, saw its market cap soar to over $200 million.
The surge in meme coin trading volume drove PancakeSwap, BNB Chain‚Äôs decentralized exchange, to outperform all decentralized exchanges in trading volume, reaching over $15.9 billion on Feb. 13.
‚ê• The Four Meme Platform
The meme culture boom in the BNB Chain ecosystem began with the emergence of the Fourmeme platform. Data from Dune reveals that over 200K unique users have engaged with Fourmeme this month alone.
‚ê•
@cz_binance
's bullposting skill
Changpeng Zhao‚Äôs CZ‚Äôs frequent updates, strategic bullposting, and engagement with the community can be thanked for piloting investors choice to the black 'n' yellow chain.
There's so much to be excited about on the BNB ecosystem.
@PancakeSwap
is a lesson to take home from this post.
Over the years, they kept building regardless of the direction the market is looking at. Today, all the effort is paying off with the amount of volume and fees it's accruing.

@PancakeSwap

content_text:
Why Was Today‚Äôs $CAKE Burn So Big‚ùì

Every Monday, PancakeSwap conducts its routine CAKE burn, removing a portion of the total supply to help maintain tokenomics and sustainability. However, today‚Äôs burn was significantly larger than usual. Here‚Äôs why.

Understanding the CAKE Minting and Burning Process

CAKE tokens are minted and temporarily held in the MasterChef V2 (MCV2) contract. This contract distributes CAKE as farm rewards when users harvest their yields. Typically, when someone claims their rewards, the system also triggers the burncake() function, which removes some of the supply.

New CAKE is only minted if MCV2 doesn‚Äôt have enough tokens to distribute. Since MCV2 is often running low, calling burncake() normally leads to the minting of millions of CAKE, with a portion allocated for burning.

What Happened Today?

During today‚Äôs burncake() call, MCV2 already had approximately 3 million CAKE available.

Key Differences in Today's Burn:
- No new CAKE was minted.
- The entire 3 million CAKE in MCV2 was sent to Burn Safe for burning.

Why Was There So Much CAKE in MCV2?

The most likely explanation is the Ecosystem Fund. These funds were minted earlier but were accumulating in MCV2 since there was no immediate need to use them. Because MCV2 had enough CAKE available for distribution, these tokens remained untouched until today's scheduled burn.

Final Thoughts

Today's burn was an unusual but positive event for CAKE‚Äôs supply dynamics. Instead of minting and burning new tokens, previously minted CAKE was directly removed from circulation. This means fewer new tokens were introduced into the system, potentially reducing inflationary pressure.

With PancakeSwap's commitment to efficient tokenomics, such events reinforce the platform‚Äôs long-term sustainability. Stay tuned for more updates on CAKE burns and supply changes!

content_text:
$CAKE PancakeSwap MEV Guard: Secure and Smart Swap Experience!!

PancakeSwap has introduced an important update to its MEV Guard feature, enhancing protection against MEV (Miner Extractable Value) attacks on the BNB Chain. With this update, support has been expanded to include Binance Wallet, Trust Wallet, OKX Wallet, and Rabby Wallet, making it even easier to trade safely.

What is MEV Guard?

MEV attacks occur when bots manipulate transactions, often leading to worse prices and failed swaps. PancakeSwap MEV Guard prevents frontrunning and sandwich attacks, ensuring a fair trading experience for all users.

Key Features

- Protection against MEV attacks for safer swaps
- Fast and reliable RPC for smooth transactions
- Free and easy setup with one-click activation
- Expanded wallet support, including Binance Wallet, Trust Wallet, OKX Wallet, MetaMask, and Rabby Wallet

How to Enable MEV Guard

Binance Wallet and Trust Wallet (Automatic Activation)
1. Connect your Binance Wallet or Trust Wallet to PancakeSwap.
2. Check for the "MEV Protected" label on the swap page.

MetaMask and OKX Wallet (One-Click Setup)
1. Visit the PancakeSwap MEV Guard page.
2. Connect your wallet.
3. Click "Enable MEV Protection" and "Add to Wallet."

Note: WalletConnect users on MetaMask are not supported.

Rabby Wallet (Manual Setup)
1. Go to the PancakeSwap MEV Guard page.
2. Click "Enable MEV Protection."
3. In Rabby Wallet settings, navigate to "Add Network" and enter the provided PancakeSwap MEV Guard RPC details.

Start Using MEV Guard Today

Activate PancakeSwap MEV Guard now to secure your trades and enjoy a seamless trading experience on the BNB Chain.

content_text:
üö®ARGENTINA‚ÄôS $LIBRA MEME COIN PLUNGES, WIPING OUT $4.4B!
LET‚ÄôS SEE WHY EVERYONE‚ÄôS TALKING ABOUT IT FOR THE PAST TWO DAYS!
going into the details in this thread üßµüëá
1/ It all started with this post at 5:01 PM ET from Javier Milei.
Just like President Trump‚Äôs memecoin launch, the first hour was filled with speculation:
Was this a hack or a real launch?
It turned out to be real as multiple Argentinian politicians confirmed the news.
2/ Right from the start, something felt off about the project.
The website claimed the launch‚Äôs goal was ‚Äúto boost the Argentine economy by funding small projects.‚Äù
The icing on the cake?
The site literally links to a Google Form to ‚Äúapply for funding.‚Äù Strange, right? ü§îüëá
3/ But it gets worse.
The website was created just hours before launch, as shown below.
The domain was registered for only 1 year, and there was no public owner information‚Äîplus, multiple restricted domain statuses.
Was this project literally created overnight? üßêüëá
4/ Within just 3 hours of the launch, insiders in $LIBRA began cashing out.
According to Bubblemaps, a massive $87.4 MILLION was cashed out within the first 3 hours.
Even worse, 82% of $LIBRA was held in one cluster, and no tokenomics were shared with the public.
But it gets even worse... üëá
5/ As Bubblemaps points out below, insiders were adding one-sided liquidity pools on Meteora using only $LIBRA.
They were removing USD and SOL and used these liquidity pools instead of selling directly on the market.
The result? $LIBRA fell 90%+ as the $87.4M in sales absorbed all buy pressure at the top. üò±üëá
6/ Within minutes of launch, multiple large holders began liquidating MILLIONS in USD worth of $LIBRA.
This included gains of $4 million or more as $LIBRA surged to a $4.6 billion market cap.
After the top was set at 5:40 PM ET, the coin plummeted in a literal straight line. üò≥üëá
7/ In fact, insiders controlled such a large portion of the market that only ~27% of transactions were sales.
This means that LARGE sale transactions were filled by smaller buys, likely from retail traders.
For every seller, there were 2 buyers, and over $1.1 BILLION in volume was traded. üí∏üëá
8/ Now, Javier Milei has stated that he was ‚Äúnot aware of the details of the project.‚Äù
He claims that after learning more, he decided to stop spreading the word and delete the post.
$LIBRA has since fallen to a new low of $200 million in market cap, erasing a staggering $4.4 BILLION. üò¨üëá
9/ The launch of $LIBRA drained so much liquidity from the market that even $TRUMP coin saw a sharp decline.
Over $500 MILLION in market cap was erased from $TRUMP after the launch.
In just the first 2 hours, more than 50,000 wallets became holders of $LIBRA. üò≥üëá
10/ This entire event has wiped out most of the liquidity in the memecoin market.
Over $6+ billion in market cap has been erased in just the last 3 hours across the market.
Are memecoins officially dead? ü§î

for more daily information.
